OL,3,C'It makes you feel inhuman': Patient
OL,4,Creveals NHS corridor care ordeal
OL,6,FPeter from Liverpool spent four hours
OL,7,Fwaiting in an ambulance, then 12 hours
OL,8,Fin an A&E corridor, followed by 18
OL,9,Fhours in another corridor. When he
OL,10,Fthought he was finally being
OL,11,Ftransferred to a ward he was, in fact,
OL,12,Fplaced in a curtained area at the end
OL,13,Fof another corridor, next to a
OL,14,Fcupboard. He spent another three days
OL,15,Fthere.
OL,17,FSpeaking to ITV News while he was
OL,18,Fstill in hospital, Peter described the
OL,19,Fexperience as "mental cruelty".
